1
00:00:07,688 --> 00:00:11,918
KOBAYASHI KAORU

2
00:00:13,388 --> 00:00:17,658
ISHIBASHI KEI

3
00:00:20,148 --> 00:00:24,518
FUCHIGAMI YASUSHI

4
00:00:24,518 --> 00:00:34,098
Kimi ga haita shiroi iki ga ima yukkuri kaze ni notte
<i>Misty white breaths you exhale, now gently riding on the wind</i>

5
00:00:34,578 --> 00:00:44,658
Sora ni ukabu kumo no naka ni sukoshi zutsu kiete yuku
<i>Into the clouds in the sky, gradually fading away</i>

6
00:00:44,939 --> 00:00:54,548
Toku takai sora no naka de te o nobasu shiroi kumo
<i>From up above in the sky white clouds reach down</i>

7
00:00:54,548 --> 00:00:56,018
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

8
00:00:56,018 --> 00:01:01,528
<i>At the end of the day, when people are rushing home...</i>
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

9
00:01:01,528 --> 00:01:04,088
<i>...That's when my day starts.</i>
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

10
00:01:04,088 --> 00:01:04,368
Kimi ga haita iki o sutte pokkari to ukan deru
<i>To inhale your exhaled breaths that float by</i>

11
00:01:05,928 --> 00:01:14,878
Zutto mukashi no koto no yoda ne
<i>Always seems like a thing of the past</i>

12
00:01:15,956 --> 00:01:20,648
Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
<i>Clouds passing over a flowing river</i>

13
00:01:20,648 --> 00:01:25,788
<i>My business hours start from midnight to 7 am.</i>
Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
<i>Clouds passing over a flowing river</i>

14
00:01:25,788 --> 00:01:26,318
Kawamo no ue o kumo ga nagareru
<i>Clouds passing over a flowing river</i>

15
00:01:26,318 --> 00:01:30,848
<i>People call my restaurant 'the late night diner.'</i>

16
00:01:34,158 --> 00:01:38,798
<i>Do customers come? You ask...
There's quite a number who do.</i>

17
00:01:41,058 --> 00:01:49,444
<i>Wabi-Sabi Subs presents:</i>
<b>SHINYA SHOKUDO Season 3</b>
EP 3: "Simmered Taro and Squid..."

18
00:02:10,308 --> 00:02:12,978
<i>During days when I make too much
amount of some simmered dish...</i>

19
00:02:12,978 --> 00:02:18,698
<i>...sometimes, I heat it up and let
the aroma waft throughout the shop.</i>

20
00:02:21,708 --> 00:02:23,898
Boiled taro and squid?

21
00:02:24,038 --> 00:02:29,028
You got it. Acute sense of smell
as always, huh? Satomi-san.

22
00:02:29,028 --> 00:02:30,558
I'll have that please.

23
00:02:30,558 --> 00:02:32,098
Ah, me too.

24
00:02:32,098 --> 00:02:34,278
Sure thing.

25
00:02:36,238 --> 00:02:38,238
<i>This is also my business tactic.</i>

26
00:02:49,378 --> 00:02:51,388
Master, it's delicious!

27
00:02:51,388 --> 00:02:53,098
Glad you like it.

28
00:02:53,098 --> 00:02:56,198
Somehow, these two make a good combination.

29
00:02:59,218 --> 00:03:01,328
Order something,
don't hold yourself back.

30
00:03:03,258 --> 00:03:07,648
No... Somehow, I don't feel like eating.

31
00:03:08,608 --> 00:03:11,388
As I thought, you're not suited for it.

32
00:03:11,388 --> 00:03:13,258
Is he a newbie?

33
00:03:13,358 --> 00:03:15,958
He's undergoing training. Sasaki-kun.

34
00:03:17,438 --> 00:03:19,998
Honestly...

35
00:03:20,248 --> 00:03:23,938
I didn't expect that much
cheating and adultery...

36
00:03:23,938 --> 00:03:26,588
...to happen so often.

37
00:03:26,588 --> 00:03:28,768
It's human instinct, isn't it?

38
00:03:28,768 --> 00:03:32,098
It's 'cause we whitewash
the shackles of marriage...

39
00:03:32,098 --> 00:03:34,258
...that's why it becomes a hassle.

40
00:03:34,258 --> 00:03:36,568
What do you guys do?

41
00:03:36,698 --> 00:03:39,848
Private investigation agency.
We investigate cheatings and such.

42
00:03:39,848 --> 00:03:41,888
Oh, you're investigators huh.

43
00:03:41,888 --> 00:03:44,288
No wonder, you have a keen nose.

44
00:03:50,878 --> 00:03:53,668
But Satomi-san...

45
00:03:53,668 --> 00:03:56,478
...why did you try this kind of work?

46
00:03:56,658 --> 00:04:00,678
I can't talk enough about such
a thing with just one bottle of alcohol.

47
00:04:00,758 --> 00:04:02,968
Master, give us more alcohol.

48
00:04:03,068 --> 00:04:05,288
I only serve up to 3 bottles, okay?

49
00:04:10,948 --> 00:04:14,998
Though he did say he couldn't hold his liquor,
didn't expect it to be this early.

50
00:04:15,118 --> 00:04:17,428
Pathetic, huh?

51
00:04:18,378 --> 00:04:20,958
He graduated from a top university...

52
00:04:20,958 --> 00:04:23,588
...and seemed to be doing his
work properly at first but...

53
00:04:23,588 --> 00:04:26,608
...somehow, he suddenly became
afraid to go to the office.

54
00:04:26,708 --> 00:04:28,218
Why?

55
00:04:28,518 --> 00:04:32,698
He says he was probably unsuccessful
in establishing human relations but...

56
00:04:32,968 --> 00:04:34,708
Of all things...

57
00:04:34,708 --> 00:04:38,508
...he wants to quit his job of
investigating the dark side of people.

58
00:04:47,458 --> 00:04:50,198
Sasaki-kun, wake up.
We're going home.

59
00:04:53,858 --> 00:04:55,928
Are you all right?

60
00:04:56,158 --> 00:04:58,378
I'm fine, I'm fine.

61
00:05:00,878 --> 00:05:02,568
Taxi!

62
00:05:02,938 --> 00:05:06,288
That kind of gal is the
"handsome" type of woman, right?

63
00:05:06,288 --> 00:05:07,988
But a gal like her...

64
00:05:07,988 --> 00:05:11,138
...doesn't want to become someone's partner.

65
00:05:11,725 --> 00:05:16,225
<i>Still, I wasn't sure what
goes on between men and women.</i>

66
00:05:36,018 --> 00:05:39,038
I never bought a takarakuji (lottery ticket).

67
00:05:39,038 --> 00:05:41,438
It's like buying "a castle in the air". Right?

68
00:05:41,688 --> 00:05:43,628
That kind of thing is a "tanuki*", isn't it?
(*craftiness; also, raccoon dog).

69
00:05:43,698 --> 00:05:44,968
"Tanuki"?

70
00:05:44,968 --> 00:05:47,538
It's just a "kara-kuji" after all.

71
00:05:49,189 --> 00:05:53,369
Look... if you take away the
"ta" from "takarakuji"...

72
00:05:53,955 --> 00:05:56,208
Oh, then it's "karakuji" (losing ticket)...

73
00:05:56,304 --> 00:05:58,814
Geez, Chuu-san, I can't laugh at your puns,
they're too confusing.

74
00:05:59,028 --> 00:06:01,228
You just lack education.

75
00:06:01,898 --> 00:06:02,668
Good evening.

76
00:06:02,668 --> 00:06:03,658
Welcome.

77
00:06:04,358 --> 00:06:05,948
- Hello.
- Hey.

78
00:06:07,178 --> 00:06:09,598
Master, beer please.

79
00:06:10,228 --> 00:06:12,928
She's the "handsome" woman
I talked about before.

80
00:06:14,398 --> 00:06:16,988
Here you go.

81
00:06:16,988 --> 00:06:20,798
That guy from before, was he okay?
He got really drunk.

82
00:06:20,938 --> 00:06:22,648
I was surprised.

83
00:06:22,748 --> 00:06:25,318
...Sasaki-kun was a virgin.

84
00:06:25,748 --> 00:06:27,168
Eh?

85
00:06:29,288 --> 00:06:32,368
Missy, you did it with him?

86
00:06:32,568 --> 00:06:35,078
Well, kinda.

87
00:06:35,078 --> 00:06:37,508
But it was his first time.

88
00:06:37,608 --> 00:06:39,698
He's no longer coming to work.

89
00:06:39,698 --> 00:06:43,228
Nor replying to my emails...
I wonder if it made matters worse.

90
00:06:43,228 --> 00:06:45,868
Was it a good thing...
or a bad thing...

91
00:06:45,868 --> 00:06:47,398
Hasn't he been here?

92
00:06:47,398 --> 00:06:48,748
He hasn't.

93
00:06:49,018 --> 00:06:51,958
For now, I'm waiting for his reply.

94
00:06:54,508 --> 00:06:56,098
Sasaki-kun.

95
00:06:56,628 --> 00:06:58,828
Did you read my messages?

96
00:07:04,258 --> 00:07:06,388
Satomi-san...

97
00:07:07,758 --> 00:07:09,748
Um...

98
00:07:11,078 --> 00:07:12,858
Can we...

99
00:07:14,148 --> 00:07:17,248
...see each other
with the premise of marriage?

100
00:07:17,248 --> 00:07:18,298
What?

101
00:07:18,298 --> 00:07:22,818
Huh? Why do you want to get
married to me?

102
00:07:23,218 --> 00:07:25,778
Because that night...

103
00:07:25,978 --> 00:07:28,158
Are you stupid?

104
00:07:28,158 --> 00:07:30,948
We only slept once.

105
00:07:30,948 --> 00:07:35,038
Satomi-san, don't you like me?

106
00:07:35,298 --> 00:07:39,798
You slept with me
and yet you're not interested in me?

107
00:07:39,798 --> 00:07:42,388
Why are you saying stuff
that a woman would say?

108
00:07:42,388 --> 00:07:46,088
In the first place, I have no interest in marriage.

109
00:07:47,968 --> 00:07:52,668
My feelings, you see...
are not that simple.

110
00:07:59,108 --> 00:08:01,418
Am I right? She's "handsome", isn't she.

111
00:08:01,418 --> 00:08:03,208
She's too "handsome".

112
00:08:03,208 --> 00:08:11,938
That kind of woman may readily
open up her body but... not her heart.

113
00:08:13,348 --> 00:08:15,838
A long time ago, there was...

114
00:08:16,128 --> 00:08:21,498
...a pure girl who never suspected anyone.

115
00:08:21,898 --> 00:08:26,178
That girl had a wonderful fiancé.

116
00:08:27,188 --> 00:08:30,928
One day, the girl had seen her fiancé...

117
00:08:30,928 --> 00:08:34,398
...get inside a cab by chance...

118
00:08:34,898 --> 00:08:37,408
Feeling mischievous...

119
00:08:37,408 --> 00:08:40,938
...she thought to try and follow the cab.

120
00:08:41,488 --> 00:08:44,588
It's 'cause the girl loved detective dramas.

121
00:08:47,428 --> 00:08:49,408
And then...

122
00:08:50,708 --> 00:08:52,568
...what happened?

123
00:08:52,838 --> 00:08:55,158
The girl...

124
00:08:55,634 --> 00:08:58,434
...saw where her fiancé does his cheating.

125
00:09:02,388 --> 00:09:04,848
From then on...

126
00:09:04,848 --> 00:09:08,798
...she tailed the fiancé on a daily basis.

127
00:09:09,278 --> 00:09:13,548
Eventually, she got addicted
to the tailing itself...

128
00:09:14,401 --> 00:09:17,651
That's how she came to work
in a detective agency.

129
00:09:22,888 --> 00:09:28,508
And... the fiancé?

130
00:09:28,858 --> 00:09:31,318
The girl collected proofs of cheating...

131
00:09:31,318 --> 00:09:36,418
...claimed palimony,
and canceled the engagement.

132
00:09:36,418 --> 00:09:38,298
Sasaki-kun.

133
00:09:39,248 --> 00:09:40,608
Yes.

134
00:09:42,198 --> 00:09:47,158
A person cannot survive if he is not strong.

135
00:10:39,490 --> 00:10:42,190
Here. Next is a cheating investigation.

136
00:10:43,538 --> 00:10:46,258
Why do people make mistakes?

137
00:10:48,944 --> 00:10:53,505
I'd like to think that if mistakes are impenetrable,
it would become the correct answer.

138
00:10:53,770 --> 00:10:55,290
You have a point.

139
00:10:56,120 --> 00:11:00,190
Say, why don't we let
Sasaki-kun handle this one?

140
00:11:00,190 --> 00:11:01,660
Him?

141
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:02,552
Yeah.

142
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:05,997
It'll be his graduation exam to
become regular employee.

143
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:14,850
Is that Karei no nitsuke (simmered flounder)?

144
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:17,680
Sorry. Here you go.

145
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:19,830
I was close.
Difference is that it's "Kareh", huh?
(Curry or "karee" and "karei" almost sound the same)

146
00:11:19,830 --> 00:11:22,230
Weren't you totally way off the mark?

147
00:11:22,230 --> 00:11:24,250
How's work going?

148
00:11:24,570 --> 00:11:29,010
Well... it's tiring but...
somehow, I'm doing okay.

149
00:11:29,670 --> 00:11:31,960
However, Satomi-san...

150
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:35,610
...had been cold to me ever since that day....

151
00:11:35,610 --> 00:11:39,480
Really? When she came here
alone the other day...

152
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:44,790
...she praised you by saying,
"He's been working really hard".

153
00:11:44,790 --> 00:11:46,940
Is that true?

154
00:11:47,490 --> 00:11:50,490
Hopefully, if my next investigation will go well...

155
00:11:50,490 --> 00:11:54,330
...I'll formally be recognized
as an investigator.

156
00:11:54,330 --> 00:11:58,540
And then, once again...

157
00:11:58,540 --> 00:12:02,340
...I'm going to confess to Satomi-san.

158
00:12:04,490 --> 00:12:09,010
I see... She praised me huh?

159
00:12:09,010 --> 00:12:11,500
Master, hot liquor please.

160
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:13,190
Will you be okay?

161
00:12:13,190 --> 00:12:15,250
I want to drink.

162
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:18,940
Thanks for the hard work.

163
00:13:20,620 --> 00:13:22,670
It's Yoshino.

164
00:13:53,738 --> 00:13:55,938
- Welcome.
- Good evening.

165
00:13:58,878 --> 00:14:00,868
Did you wait long?

166
00:14:00,868 --> 00:14:02,558
No.

167
00:14:03,658 --> 00:14:05,498
Thanks.

168
00:14:42,898 --> 00:14:44,948
You investigated it well.

169
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:52,128
This person was my former fiance.

170
00:14:53,558 --> 00:14:57,618
Two years ago, I met him by chance
for the first time in 10 years.

171
00:14:59,598 --> 00:15:02,778
Life is a mystery, huh?

172
00:15:03,281 --> 00:15:05,839
Though I broke up with him for cheating...

173
00:15:05,998 --> 00:15:09,898
Now I'm the one who's... Right?

174
00:15:13,018 --> 00:15:17,688
Don't you think this is bad?
His wife and children, and all...

175
00:15:17,898 --> 00:15:19,688
Not at all.

176
00:15:21,448 --> 00:15:23,688
Well then, what is this for?

177
00:15:24,558 --> 00:15:26,498
This work of ours.

178
00:15:27,588 --> 00:15:29,948
This so-called "Wanting to know the truth"...

179
00:15:29,948 --> 00:15:32,168
...Isn't it human instinct?

180
00:15:36,638 --> 00:15:38,718
I don't...

181
00:15:40,191 --> 00:15:42,191
...get you.

182
00:15:43,648 --> 00:15:48,568
I realized that I am more at ease
betraying people than be betrayed.

183
00:15:48,568 --> 00:15:50,568
For the last 10 years.

184
00:15:55,889 --> 00:15:58,592
Once I report this...

185
00:15:59,444 --> 00:16:03,118
...do you know what will happen?

186
00:16:03,118 --> 00:16:04,598
Of course.

187
00:16:04,848 --> 00:16:05,718
Is that okay with you?

188
00:16:05,718 --> 00:16:07,158
Yes.

189
00:16:14,178 --> 00:16:19,248
Please let me ask one last question.

190
00:16:23,008 --> 00:16:31,348
Why are okay with this guy...
and not me?

191
00:16:37,648 --> 00:16:40,348
Maybe we're like taro and squid.

192
00:16:43,618 --> 00:16:47,338
We go well together. Somewhat.

193
00:16:55,368 --> 00:16:57,488
Excuse me.

194
00:16:59,058 --> 00:17:00,568
No need.

195
00:17:18,958 --> 00:17:20,548
Is that okay?

196
00:17:21,418 --> 00:17:23,108
Am I contemptible?

197
00:17:25,468 --> 00:17:29,568
If you do not become strong,
you won't survive, right?

198
00:17:48,058 --> 00:17:52,028
These are... the photos.

199
00:17:52,028 --> 00:17:57,978
<i>It seems Sasaki-kun, as promised,
had submitted his report.</i>

200
00:18:19,278 --> 00:18:23,758
<i>As expected, Satomi-san was
fired from the agency.</i>

201
00:18:29,945 --> 00:18:32,815
<i>And then, some time after that...</i>

202
00:18:57,678 --> 00:19:00,358
When I was organizing the data...

203
00:19:00,358 --> 00:19:02,428
...I noticed that.

204
00:19:05,718 --> 00:19:08,718
She knew we were being tailed.

205
00:19:14,928 --> 00:19:18,518
It was only a matter of time
before the wife finds out...

206
00:19:19,032 --> 00:19:22,488
...even without resorting to
investigation agencies...

207
00:19:22,488 --> 00:19:25,488
...she doubted me considerably...

208
00:19:25,488 --> 00:19:28,418
I too thought it's better if I got caught somewhere...

209
00:19:36,118 --> 00:19:40,188
I had also thought about it seriously...

210
00:19:40,188 --> 00:19:42,588
...that if we continue to be together,
I'll be headed for a divorce.

211
00:19:46,655 --> 00:19:51,825
Then why...
if Satomi-san knew you're being tailed...

212
00:19:56,586 --> 00:20:00,326
That night, in the hotel...

213
00:20:01,628 --> 00:20:04,398
At first, she was crying...

214
00:20:04,708 --> 00:20:06,848
...and was saying...

215
00:20:07,408 --> 00:20:10,708
"I betrayed my old self".

216
00:20:14,328 --> 00:20:17,338
This is her way of taking responsibility.

217
00:20:17,508 --> 00:20:22,708
Also for me... and for you...

218
00:20:22,708 --> 00:20:25,008
...she made herself become the bad guy.

219
00:20:37,558 --> 00:20:41,458
She showed herself to me on purpose.

220
00:20:45,992 --> 00:20:47,992
She was a good woman.

221
00:20:49,288 --> 00:20:52,688
A great deal more of a man than me.

222
00:21:09,635 --> 00:21:12,535
This one's on the house.
To celebrate your promotion.

223
00:21:18,068 --> 00:21:19,768
Women...

224
00:21:20,888 --> 00:21:22,758
...I really don't get them.

225
00:21:22,758 --> 00:21:24,518
Oh, well.

226
00:21:26,528 --> 00:21:28,418
But...

227
00:21:29,648 --> 00:21:34,928
...she has made me a man, I think.

228
00:21:34,928 --> 00:21:36,928
I see.

229
00:21:39,458 --> 00:21:43,708
I will for sure...

230
00:21:43,931 --> 00:21:45,761
...find Satomi-san.

231
00:21:47,608 --> 00:21:51,178
Is there anything you want to eat?

232
00:21:57,540 --> 00:22:00,308
Boiled taro...

233
00:22:00,308 --> 00:22:02,528
...and squid?

234
00:22:02,768 --> 00:22:05,748
Your nose is getting a bit keener, huh?

235
00:22:11,048 --> 00:22:12,768
Hey, Daigo, let's go!

236
00:22:12,768 --> 00:22:14,768
Yeah, I know.

237
00:22:16,808 --> 00:22:17,978
Wow...

238
00:22:17,978 --> 00:22:19,458
Cool.

239
00:22:36,828 --> 00:22:40,568
Wow~! Cool!!

240
00:22:40,868 --> 00:22:42,738
That was awesome!

241
00:22:49,928 --> 00:22:53,098
First, slightly boil the squid, than remove.

242
00:22:53,098 --> 00:22:55,648
Before the taro are done cooking,
put back the squid again...

243
00:22:55,648 --> 00:22:58,598
...and cook until the taro becomes
soft and not hard.

244
00:22:58,598 --> 00:23:01,198
By the way, instead of using
hot water for taro...

245
00:23:01,198 --> 00:23:05,680
...use the boiled squid's seasoned liquid so
you won't get bothered by the taro's sliminess.

246
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:07,680
Thanks for waiting.

